
Intune Auto-Enrollment vs. Windows Autopilot
Feature	Intune Automatic Enrollment	Windows Autopilot Enrollment
What it is	Background device enrollment into Intune when a user signs in.	Deployment service that provisions new or re-purposed devices during OOBE.
When it happens	After a user signs in to Windows with an Entra ID (Azure AD) account (if in MDM scope).	During Out-of-Box Experience (OOBE) on first boot or after device reset.
Requires reset?	âŒ No reset needed â€“ works on existing devices.	âœ… Yes â€“ must go through OOBE â†’ requires new device or device reset. Restart alone wonâ€™t work.
Trigger steps	1. In Intune admin center â†’ Devices â†’ Windows enrollment â†’ Automatic enrollment.2. Set MDM user scope = All or group.3. User signs in â†’ device auto-enrolls silently.	1. Import hardware hash (OEM, Intune, PowerShell).2. Assign Autopilot deployment profile.3. Reset device (Wipe, Fresh Start, or Autopilot Reset).4. Device boots into OOBE and applies profile.
Device visibility	Device appears in Intune â†’ Devices list once enrolled.	Device appears in Intune and is also marked as Autopilot registered.
End-user experience	Transparent; no OOBE or re-setup required.	Guided OOBE with optional branding, user type (admin/standard), app installs, and Enrollment Status Page.
Customization	Apply Intune MDM policies, compliance rules, apps, security baselines.	Preconfigure device naming, user account type, OEM branding, ESP, apps, and enrollment options.
Ideal for	Managing existing devices already in use (no data loss).	New devices or re-purposed devices where standardized provisioning is needed.
